  "prompt": "How should I start preparing for CLAT 2017?",
  "response": "Preparing for the Common Law Admission Test (CLAT) requires a well-structured plan and consistent efforts. Here are some steps to help you start your preparation for CLAT 2017:\n\n1. **Understand the Exam Pattern and Syllabus**:\n   - Familiarize yourself with the exam pattern, number of questions, and marking scheme.\n   - The CLAT typically includes sections on English, General Knowledge and Current Affairs, Elementary Mathematics, Legal Aptitude, and Logical Reasoning.\n\n2. **Collect Study Material**:\n   - Gather relevant books, previous years' question papers, sample papers, and other study materials. Recommended books include Pearson's guide to CLAT, Universal's guide to CLAT, and books for individual sections.\n\n3. **Create a Study Plan**:\n   - Develop a study schedule that allocates time for each subject based on your strengths and weaknesses. Ensure you dedicate time to regular revision and practice.\n\n4. **Focus on Each Section**:\n   - **English**: Improve your grammar, vocabulary, and comprehension skills. Practice reading comprehension and critical reasoning questions.\n   - **General Knowledge and Current Affairs**: Stay updated with the latest news, read newspapers daily, and refer to monthly magazines for current affairs.\n   - **Elementary Mathematics**: Brush up on basic mathematics concepts and practice problems regularly.\n   - **Legal Aptitude**: Understand basic legal principles, legal terms, and solve questions on legal reasoning.\n   - **Logical Reasoning**: Solve puzzles, practice logical reasoning questions, and work on improving analytical skills.\n\n5. **Practice Regularly**:\n   - Solve previous years' question papers and take mock tests to get an idea of the exam's difficulty level and your time management skills.\n   - Analyze your performance and work on weak areas.\n\n6. **Time Management**:\n   - Practice managing your time during preparation as well as on the exam day. This helps in efficiently completing questions within the given timeframe.\n\n7. **Stay Motivated and Positive**:\n   - Stay focused on your goal and maintain a positive attitude. Take breaks, stay healthy, and avoid stress.\n\n8. **Join Coaching if Necessary**:\n   - If self-study seems challenging, consider joining a coaching institute for guidance and structured preparation.\n\n9. **Revise Regularly**:\n   - Revision is crucial. Keep revising all topics periodically to keep them fresh in your memory.\n\nRemember, consistency and regular practice are key to successful preparation for CLAT. Good luck!",
